&lt;p&gt;I have a variable in PHP, and I need its value in my JavaScript code. How can I get my variable from PHP to JavaScript?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have code that looks like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-php s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-php&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-meta&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;?php&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$val&lt;/span&gt; = &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-variable&quot;&gt;$myService&lt;/span&gt;-&amp;gt;&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_ invoke__&quot;&gt;getValue&lt;/span&gt;(); &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// Makes an API and database call&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;p&gt;On the same page, I have JavaScript code that needs the value of the &lt;code&gt;$val&lt;/code&gt; variable to be passed as a parameter:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;lang-js s-code-block&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;hljs language-javascript&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;script&amp;gt;
    myPlugin.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;start&lt;/span&gt;($val); &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// I tried this, but it didn&apos;t work&lt;/span&gt;
    &amp;lt;?php myPlugin.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;start&lt;/span&gt;($val); ?&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// This didn&apos;t work either&lt;/span&gt;
    myPlugin.&lt;span class=&quot;hljs-title function_&quot;&gt;start&lt;/span&gt;(&amp;lt;?=$val?&amp;gt;); &lt;span class=&quot;hljs-comment&quot;&gt;// This works sometimes, but sometimes it fails&lt;/span&gt;
&amp;lt;/script&amp;gt;
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
